apo Ndori, claimed gold in 2:59.11, setting the fastest time this year.\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 1011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.456867591956718e-11, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 881, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Collen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collen\"}, {\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leungo_Scotch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leungo Scotch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leungo_Scotch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leungo_Scotch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgium's team secured the bronze medal with a time of 3:01.16.\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9642988755621847, \"rank\": 0.036997090045405176, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The South African men's 4\\u00d7100 m\\u00a0relay team\\u00a0faced a setback during the first qualifying round, failing to secure a spot for the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, they bounced back in the second qualifying round, with Bayanda Walaza, Benjamin Richardson, Bradley Nkoana, and Akani Simbine winning their qualifier in an impressive time of 38.08 seconds.\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1300, \"end\": 1308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.9411213961894122, \"rank\": 0.05439379592310688, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 1309, \"end\": 1319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9980834588499011, \"rank\": 0.0019202155909273254, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"score\": 0.9741216700036883, \"rank\": 0.01810947847476777, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\"}, {\"begin\": 1341, \"end\": 1354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This performance not only earned them a place in the Paris Olympics but also recorded the fastest overall time in the second qualifying round.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the men's 4\\u00d7100 m\\u00a0relay team\\u00a0did not advance to the finals in Nassau, their time in the second qualifying round would have been good enough for a bronze medal in the finals.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"score\": 0.9855728340375995, \"rank\": 0.014259250172683783, \"text\": \"Nassau\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American team, consisting of Courtney Lindsey, Kenneth Bednarek, Kyree King, and Noah Lyles, dominated the finals with a world-leading time of 37.40.\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1752, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999925199351853, \"rank\": 7.4651355767206186e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\", \"score\": 0.9999994804831189, \"rank\": 5.195172025866465e-07, \"text\": \"Courtney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\"}, {\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Lindsey\", \"score\": 0.9827194954196645, \"rank\": 0.01746593372325139, \"text\": \"Lindsey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Lindsey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Lindsey\"}, {\"begin\": 1799, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenneth Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}, {\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyree_King\", \"score\": 0.9999999741885407, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kyree King\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyree_King\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/